ertainment. \n \nA 13-episode anime adaptation produced by J.C.Staff aired between July and October 2003, on AT-X and other channels. A second anime season produced by Arms aired on AT-X between February and May 2007, spanning twelve episodes. A third anime season, also produced by Arms, aired on AT-X between June and August 2008, spanning twelve episodes and featuring an all-new plotline and characters. A fourth anime season produced by TNK and Arms aired on AT-X and other channels between March and June 2010, spanning 12 episodes and introducing new schools and characters. An anime OVA was announced by Media Factory, and premiered in Japanese theaters on November 12, 2011. \n \nThe first anime season was licensed in North America by Geneon Entertainment, but it is now licensed by Funimation after Geneon withdrew from the anime market. The second anime season is licensed in North America by Media Blasters. The third anime season was also licensed by Media Blasters,but it is now licensed by Funimation. The fourth anime season is also licensed by Funimation.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"themes":[1],"genres":[4],"first_release_date":1191283200000,"platforms":[8],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":8,"date":1191283200000,"region":8,"human":"2007-Oct-02","y":2007,"m":10}],"alternative_names":[{"name":"Battle Vixens","comment":"American title"}]},{"id":44646,"name":"K-1 Premium Dynamite!!","slug":"k-1-premium-dynamite","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/k-1-premium-dynamite","created_at":1499431151709,"updated_at":1500550951706,"popularity":1.0,"category":0,"genres":[4],"first_release_date":1106352000000,"platforms":[8],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":8,"date":1106352000000,"region":8,"human":"2005-Jan-22","y":2005,"m":1}]},{"id":44647,"name":"Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja 4","slug":"naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-4--1","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-4--1","created_at":1499431154853,"updated_at":15278