rt, Racquetball, was released in 1981 for the Atari Video Computer System. A1 Games' history of released sports related games includes tennis, boxing, bowling, kickboxing, snowboarding, racing and more. \n \nAs in indoor racquetball courts, Street Racquetball's \"outdoor\" courts contain two sidewalls, a front wall, serving zones, and a receiving line -- but no ceiling. Players can opt for exhibition mode (against the computer), challenge mode (unlock new characters and courts by winning three consecutive matches), training mode (continuous rally solo play), or two-player VS mode. Three difficulty settings offer \"easy,\" \"normal.\" or \"hard\" gameplay, ball bounce levels can be adjusted to \"low,\" \"middle,\" or \"high,\" and the eight computer-controlled opponents are rated in performance level, type of game, power, speed, and skill. Shots include slams, lobs, and drop shots.","collection":3082,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[81145,30830,15851,22690,27081,75694,102122,54662,102805,22425],"tags":[268435470,536872078,536872673,536875176,536875271,536875284,536875453,536875488,536875941,536876719,536882429,536882807],"category":0,"keywords":[1166,1761,4264,4359,4372,4541,4576,5029,5807,11517,11895],"genres":[14],"first_release_date":1044576000000,"platforms":[7],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":7,"date":1044576000000,"region":8,"human":"2003-Feb-07","y":2003,"m":2}],"alternative_names":[{"name":"Simple 1500 Series Vol. 97: The Squash","comment":"Other"}],"videos":[{"name":"Gameplay video","video_id":"mbvYGk0KgoY"}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/e5it33w5mskyon7v5bpt.jpg","cloudinary_id":"e5it33w5mskyon7v5bpt","width":200,"height":197},"esrb":{"rating":3}},{"id":44913,"name":"Super Shot Soccer","slug":"super-shot-soccer","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/super-shot-soccer","created_at":1499443306657,"updated_at":1515839910369,"summary":"Tecmo's Super Shot Soccer is a hybrid of simulation and arcade-styled soccer. Featuring over 30 teams from around the world, the game's play modes are based on international-styled soccer. The four play modes are Test Mode (exhibition play), World Tournament Play (inspired by soccer's World Cup), International League (a round-robin league) and International Cup (a 16 team tournament). Of these modes, only Test Mode allows two players to play the game at the same time. \n \nDiffering itself from typical soccer simulation titles, Super Shot Soccer provides over the top arcade-style plays. Called Super Shot Special Moves, each team has two or three special moves that tie into the team's nationality. These provide a unique twist to simulation soccer, as gameplay can be interrupted by national monuments, disaster attacks and more. Special moves can be used to affect both offensive and defensive strategies.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[18681,77576,76999,72888,72833,63514,62335,62325,59802,58577],"tags":[268435470,536870938],"category":0,"keywords":[26],"genres":[14],"first_release_date":1026604800000,"platforms":[7],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":7,"date":1026604800000,"region":8,"human":"2002-Jul-14","y":2002,"m":7}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/xrewdfskdhfqqcyhkpjk.jpg","cloudinary_id":"xrewdfskdhfqqcyhkpjk","width":240,"height":210}},{"id":44914,"name":"Superstars Dance Club #1 Hits","slug":"superstars-dance-club-number-1-hits","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/superstars-dance-club-number-1-hits","created_at":1499443308841,"updated_at":1500536244948,"summary":"In Superstar Dance Club, players control 18-year old Suzy as she strives to become the Super Star Dance Club Champion of Tokyo by perfecting her rhythmic dance skills during 21 stages at various clubs. By earning a high passing grade in each stage, new stages are unlocked and Suzy earns money (chips) that determine which of the multiple endings are achieved at the end of the game. \n \nThree difficulty levels (easy, intermediate, and expert)