ish them. Supply units are unloaded while a ship docks at the player's port. Information about ongoing events is displayed in a ticker tape on the bottom of the screen.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[39257,55029,2015,12982,22399,9789,29173,30229,55036,76066],"tags":[268435467,268435471,536870913,536872383,536874694,536875171],"category":0,"keywords":[1,1471,3782,4259],"genres":[11,15]},{"id":45378,"name":"PudPud","slug":"pudpud","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/pudpud","created_at":1499505665872,"updated_at":1500536573164,"summary":"Pud Pud in Weird World (also known simply as Pud Pud) is a computer game published by Ocean Software in 1984 for the ZX Spectrum. It was written by Jonathan Smith. Smith was paid £1000 for Pud Pud by Ocean Software and was given a job at Ocean as a direct result of the game. \n \n \nThe player controls Pud Pud (who resembles a round pudding with wings or feet depending on whether he's walking or flying) and must explore the maze-like Weird World. Pud Pud has a limited amount of energy which needs to be topped up by eating certain creatures that live in Weird World although other creatures, which drain his energy if eaten, must be avoided.[1] If Pud Pud runs out of energy he loses one of his three lives. \n \nMrs Pud Pud occasionally appears on the screen and is similar to Pud Pud but white and wearing high heels. If she touches Pud Pud he loses a life instantly, regardless of his energy status although the player will receive a bonus score based on how much energy was remaining when Mrs Pud Pud delivered her kiss.[1] \n \nPud Pud can obtain an extra life by collecting all ten hidden puddings.[1] \n \nThe puddings are spread randomly through the maze with only one being in the maze at a time. When all ten are collected, Pud Pud can escape Weird World.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0},{"id":45379,"name":"Star Wars: Attack on the Death Star","slug":"star-wars-attack-on-the-death-star","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/star-wars-attack-on-the-death-star","created_at":1499505668368,"updated_at":1516640937465,"summary":"Star Wars: Attack on the Death Star recreates the final battle from \"Star Wars\", putting the player at the controls of an X-Wing starfighter in full 3D. Engage in dogfights with TIE Fighters as you approach the station, and skim Death Star's surface while dodging turbolaser towers and shoot the torpedo run down the trench. \n \nAttack on the Death Star features digitized voices and 3D wireframe vector graphics!","collection":2172,"franchise":1,"franchises":[1],"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[68287,10209,10213,28029,36950,64204,10210,10212,27314,71455],"tags":[18,268435461,536871078,536871882],"developers":[13696],"publishers":[4290],"category":0,"keywords":[166,970],"themes":[18],"genres":[5],"first_release_date":695260800000,"platforms":[121],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":121,"date":695260800000,"region":8,"human":"1992-Jan-13","y":1992,"m":1}],"screenshots":[{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/njwl0mjf2nn6br6wrzm4.jpg","cloudinary_id":"njwl0mjf2nn6br6wrzm4","width":1440,"height":964}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/brhnpautj05mid1au82c.jpg","cloudinary_id":"brhnpautj05mid1au82c","width":640,"height":899}},{"id":45380,"name":"Aquales","slug":"aquales","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/aquales","created_at":1499505670987,"updated_at":1516574265171,"summary":"In the year 2069, the British ship \"Elias Rits\" sailed to Kermadec Island on a private investigation mission. Shortly thereafter, satellites reported that beacon transmissions from the ship have stopped. Seeing that further investigation required exploration of hostile environment and deep sea, the authorities dispatched a special team known as W-ODL to find out what has happened to the ship. Navigating a powerful mecha, the American pilot Fredric von Nyuya has to get to the bottom of the mystery and report his findings to the crew. \n \nAquales is an action platformer. The mecha is equipped with a default fist-like melee weapon and gains access to other methods of destruction later, including chainguns, rockets, homing missiles, and more exotic items such as a gravity flamethrower. The stages usually consist of series of platforms and are fairly large, with optional areas and power-ups (health, one-time attacks, etc.) in treasure chests. The protagonist's stand-out equipment is the grappling hook, which must be used frequently to access high platforms. The game also has a light RPG angle: the hero gains experience points from defeating enemies and levels up as a result. Each stage ends with a boss battle, after which the player's progress is saved.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[1070,1073,1188,10039,36608,74863,1066,34919,51485,26848],"tags":[1,268435464],"category":0,"themes":[1],"genres":[8],"first_release_date":687225600000,"platforms":[121],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":121,"date":687225600000,"region":8,"human":"1991-Oct-12","y":1991,"m":10}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/k3d48nobsomuvycfsm3h.jpg","cloudinary_id":"k3d48nobsomuvycfsm3h","width":400,"height":567}},{"id":45381,"name":"Bomberman Special","slug":"bomberman-special","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/bomberman-special","created_at":1499505674992,"updated_at":1500536597304,"summary":"Bomberman Special is an MSX release in the Bomberman series of games. It was brought without a license to the SG-1000 in Taiwan.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0,"themes":[1],"first_release_date":444441600000,"platforms":[84],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":84,"date":444441600000,"region":8,"human":"1984-Feb-01","y":1984,"m":2}]},{"id":45382,"name":"Astrododge","slug":"astrododge","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/astrododge","created_at":1499505678927,"updated_at":1500536598237,"summary":"Astrododge is an unlicensed SG-1000/SC-3000 game developed and published by Revival Studios. It was released in early 2013 - two and a half decades after the last officially licensed SG-1000 game, The Black Onyx in 1987. The game is relatively simple - all the user must do is dodge asteroids while travelling upwards. The game is available in both cartridge and cassette form. \n \nThe SG-1000 is one of many platforms to receive this game. The basic concept was created by Revival Studios in 2008 for CHIP-8 compatible systems of the late 1970s before being retooled for the Magnavox/Philips Odyssey² in 2011. Near identical copies to this SG-1000 version are available for the ColecoVision and MSX.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[36608,2940,40524,34919,71581,29660,1070,23175,76438,16468],"tags":[1],"category":0,"themes":[1],"first_release_date":1363910400000,"platforms":[84],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":84,"date":1363910400000,"region":8,"human":"2013-Mar-22","y":2013,"m":3}]},{"id":45383,"name":"Terebi Oekaki","slug":"terebi-oekaki","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/terebi-oekaki","created_at":1499505682919,"updated_at":1516723099558,"summary":"Terebi Oekaki is the game packaged with the Sega Graphic Board for the SG-1000. It is a simple paint program.","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[34919,36608,16468,23175,59516,28029,55289,40524,68324,10039],"tags":[1,34,536871446,536871737,536873991,536875422,536876102],"category":0,"keywords":[534,825,3079,4510,5190],"themes":[1,34],"first_release_date":507600000000,"platforms":[84],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":84,"date":507600000000,"region":8,"human":"1986-Feb-01","y":1986,"m":2}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/qotm0szhway5qrb4tflg.jpg","cloudinary_id":"qotm0szhway5qrb4tflg","width":684,"height":599}},{"id":45384,"name":"Space Mountain","slug":"space-mountain","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/space-mountain","created_at":1499505689277,"updated_at":1516590969432,"summary":"Space Mountain is an SG-1000 game developed and published by Tsukuda Original with th