ime, Taiga and Boltz, co-exists as enemy characters alongside Jakō's sons from the manga, Jask and Sheeno, while Bronza, a character exclusive to this game, serves as the General of the Red Light in place of Shoki, who filled the same role in the anime. While Shoki himself never appears in the game, his death at the hands of Sheeno is acknowledged in the official strategy guide. The game only covers the Tentei story arc, with a bonus stage featuring the Nameless Asura as a hidden final boss.","storyline":"After the death of Raoh, the Central Imperial Capital began its rule of the chaotic world under the name of the Heavenly Emperor. Now grown up, Bat and Lin has formed a resistance under the banner of Hokuto. Kenshiro returns once again after hearing the plight of the people. Kenshiro must hurry to the Imperial Capital and defeat their leader Falco of the Gento Kō Ken style.","collection":3200,"franchise":1123,"franchises":[1123],"popularity":1.666666666666667,"games":[2558,10039,51464,55752,36911,64171,28029,25311,76229,54842],"tags":[1,18,268435460,268435464,536870926,536870973,536870981,536873299,536874038,536875053,536875054,536875073,536875222,536876712,1073741828],"developers":[1819],"publishers":[1996],"category":0,"player_perspectives":[4],"game_modes":[1],"keywords":[14,61,69,2387,3126,4141,4142,4161,4310,5800],"themes":[1,18],"genres":[4,8],"first_release_date":545616000000,"platforms":[51,18],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":18,"date":607392000000,"region":2,"human":"1989-Apr-01","y":1989,"m":4},{"category":0,"platform":51,"date":545616000000,"region":5,"human":"1987-Apr-17","y":1987,"m":4}],"alternative_names":[{"name":"Hokuto no Ken 2","comment":"Other"},{"name":"Hokuto no Ken II: Seikimatsu Kyuuseishu Densetsu","comment":"Other"},{"name":"北斗の拳2 世紀末救世主伝説","comment":"Japanese title"},{"name":"Hokuto no Ken 2 Seikimatsu Kyūseishu Densetsu","comment":"Japanese title"},{"name":"Fist of the North Star","comment":"Acronym"}],"screenshots":[{"url":"//