ch shipped with some variants of the Japanese Wondermega. When hooked up to a Mega Drive connected to the Sega Mega-CD (or a Wondermega), a specific but presently unknown (possibly Sony-made, JVC-made, or Aplix-made) type of book-on-CD can be played. As with other Wondermega-related products, the cartridge features Wonder Dog heavily. It is unknown whether or not any emulator can use a cart-boot feature to run this game (some do support Flux, which works similarly, so it is possible).","popularity":1.0,"category":0},{"id":45606,"name":"Yu Yu Hakusho Gaiden","slug":"yu-yu-hakusho-gaiden--1","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/yu-yu-hakusho-gaiden--1","created_at":1499511213319,"updated_at":1500503034509,"summary":"Yuu Yuu Hakusho Gaiden (幽☆遊☆白書 外伝) is a 1994 adventure game by Nextech under contract from Sega for the Sega Mega Drive, made with the Yuu Yuu Hakusho license.","popularity":1.0,"category":0,"genres":[31],"first_release_date":762048000000,"platforms":[29],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":29,"date":762048000000,"region":8,"human":"1994-Feb-24","y":1994,"m":2}]},{"id":45607,"name":"Yuu Yuu Hakusho - Makyou Toitsusen","slug":"yuu-yuu-hakusho-makyou-toitsusen","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/yuu-yuu-hakusho-makyou-toitsusen","created_at":1499511216996,"updated_at":1513001829576,"summary":"Yuu Yuu Hakusho: Makyou Toitsusen (幽☆遊☆白書 魔強統一戦) is a 1994 fighting game for the Sega Mega Drive by Treasure made with the Yuu Yuu Hakusho license — the second such game, after Nextech's adventure game Yuu Yuu Hakusho Gaiden. Interestingly, TecToy published the game in Brazil as Yuu Yuu Hakusho: Sunset Fighters, however the game has not been released elsewhere. M.I.J.E.T. fan-translated the game to English in 2007. \n \nThe game is a 4-player fighting game. A and B attack and C blocks, with various combos along the way. Up jumps.","collection":3874,"popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[13189,25646,56987,6685,11296,2558,55935,12198,55028,26914],"tags":[19,268435460,536870990,536871019,536872032,536873021,536875054,536875198,536875199,536875941,536876650,536882677],"category":0,"keywords":[78,107,1120,2109,4142,4286,4287,5029,5738,11765],"themes":[19],"genres":[4],"first_release_date":783475200000,"platforms":[29],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":29,"date":783475200000,"region":8,"human":"1994-Oct-30","y":1994,"m":10}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/schohpsy18asynnw5u9b.jpg","cloudinary_id":"schohpsy18asynnw5u9b","width":279,"height":400}},{"id":45608,"name":"Zan Yasha Enbukyoku","slug":"zan-yasha-enbukyoku","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/zan-yasha-enbukyoku","created_at":1499511219643,"updated_at":1500503035212,"summary":"Zan Yasha Enbukyoku (斬 夜叉円舞曲) is a 1990 strategy game for the Sharp X68000 by Wolf Team in their Zan series of strategy games. They ported it to the Sega Mega Drive in 1991. No version has left Japan.","popularity":1.0,"category":0,"genres":[15],"first_release_date":688176000000,"platforms":[29],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":29,"date":688176000000,"region":8,"human":"1991-Oct-23","y":1991,"m":10}]},{"id":45609,"name":"Sansan","slug":"sansan","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/sansan","created_at":1499511222303,"updated_at":1500503035397,"summary":"Sansan (サンサン) is an online service allowing people living in Japan to play the abstract strategy board game Go with other subscribers over the internet on a Windows PC. However, at its launch in 1994, a version for the Sega Mega Drive was also made available. This version of the game allows players who have a Sega Mega Modem to connect over a 33.3kbps or ISDN line to play other members who have a Sansan ID. However, as of 2011, there are no known Mega Drive-compatible Sansan servers. A local two-player version of the game is also included for play. \n \nFor whatever reason, the Mega Drive version did not last very long — it is one of the rarest and most sought-after Mega Drive games; Sega of Japan's official archive