e pile reaches the top of the screen. In order to clear panels, three or more panels of the same color must be lined up together either vertically or horizontally. Use the D-pad to slide panels (each button indicates what direction to slide to, so the appropriate panel is automatically chosen) and A to bring the next row up immediately. A new life is awarded every 10000 points.","popularity":1.0,"games":[60044,25222,14047,19222,41348,26223,10225,27266,83207,83155],"tags":[268435465,536873787],"category":0,"keywords":[2875],"genres":[9],"first_release_date":661824000000,"platforms":[29],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":29,"date":661824000000,"region":8,"human":"1990-Dec-22","y":1990,"m":12}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/fiw82njoocyxpddf7tmv.jpg","cloudinary_id":"fiw82njoocyxpddf7tmv","width":600,"height":831}},{"id":45721,"name":"Medal City","slug":"medal-city","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/medal-city","created_at":1499513396045,"updated_at":1516630601970,"summary":"Medal City is a card game for the Sega Mega Drive, released exclusively in Japan in 1991 via the Sega Game Toshokan service. You choose between three gambling games; Poker, Blackjack, and Slots. The goal of each game (besides poker) is to earn over 100,000 medals. You will then see the game's ending (except poker, as the game never ends).","popularity":1.0,"games":[19376,76110,77483,62222,57867,51121,19290,19934,73540,69973],"tags":[536871066,536871533,536871641,536875046,536875075,536875182,536879971],"category":0,"keywords":[154,621,729,4134,4163,4270,9059],"first_release_date":665366400000,"platforms":[29],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":29,"date":665366400000,"region":8,"human":"1991-Feb-01","y":1991,"m":2}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/qhgndx7jqehlkovfvb4j.jpg","cloudinary_id":"qhgndx7jqehlkovfvb4j","width":540,"height":405}},{"id":45722,"name":"Mamono Hunter Youko: Dai 7 no Keishou","slug":"mamono-hunter-youko-dai-7